<p class="explanation">
  Your operating system and browser can provide your code with your “Device Pixel Ratio”. I have read that this number is useful when working with high resolution displays that actually can draw things at half-pixels. Your browser's current DPR is: <span id="dpr-value">unknown</span> (refresh with the window on a different screen to update).
</p>
<p class="explanation">
  The width and height of the canvas below is <code class="inline-code">100 * DPR</code>. On a high resolution DPR 2 display (like an Apple “retina” display) you should see crisp lines, on a standard DPR 1 display you should see the same blurry lines (screenshots below.)
</p>

<pre><code>
  canvas.width = 100 * dpr;
  canvas.height = 100 * dpr;
  ctx.scale(dpr, dpr);
</code></pre>

